Step 1: Compute distances
- Distance1 = 60 mph × 2 h = 120 miles
- Distance2 = 80 mph × 1 h = 80 miles

Step 2: Total distance
- Total distance = 120 + 80 = 200 miles

Step 3: Total time
- Total time = 2 h + 1 h = 3 h

Step 4: Average speed
- Average speed = Total distance / Total time = 200 miles / 3 h = 200/3 mph ≈ 66.7 mph

Answer: 200/3 mph (about 66 2/3 mph).
